## Directory layout (do not deviate)

```
src/
  components/        # Shared, reusable UI components
  pages/             # Route-level components (one per route)
  hooks/             # Custom hooks (useXxx.ts)
  lib/
    api/             # Axios client + per-resource API functions
    queryKeys.ts     # All React Query key factories
  types/             # Shared TypeScript types mirroring API schemas
  router.tsx         # React Router route definitions
```

## Component conventions

- One component per file. Filename matches the exported component (PascalCase).
- Use named exports — not default exports — for all components except route-level pages.
- Define props with a TypeScript `type` alias immediately above the component.
- Keep components small. If a component exceeds ~100 lines, split it.

```tsx
// Correct
type RecipeCardProps = {
  recipe: Recipe;
  onDelete?: (id: number) => void;
};

export function RecipeCard({ recipe, onDelete }: RecipeCardProps) { ... }

// Wrong — avoid
export default function RecipeCard(props: any) { ... }
```

## Forms

- Use React Hook Form + Zod for all forms. Zod schema is the source of truth for validation.
- Infer the form type from the Zod schema via `z.infer<typeof schema>`.
- Use `@hookform/resolvers/zod` to wire the resolver.
- Never manage form field state with `useState`.

```tsx
import { useForm } from 'react-hook-form';
import { zodResolver } from '@hookform/resolvers/zod';
import { z } from 'zod';

const schema = z.object({
  title: z.string().min(1, 'Title is required'),
  servings: z.number().min(1),
});

type FormValues = z.infer<typeof schema>;

export function RecipeForm({ onSubmit }: { onSubmit: (values: FormValues) => void }) {
  const { register, handleSubmit, formState: { errors } } = useForm<FormValues>({
    resolver: zodResolver(schema),
  });
  ...
}
```

## Type conventions

Mirror the backend schema naming in `src/types/`:

- `*Base` — shared fields (rarely needed on the frontend).
- `*Create` — POST request body shapes.
- `*Update` — PATCH/PUT request body shapes (partial fields).
- `*Read` — API response shapes (includes `id`, timestamps, nested reads).

```ts
// src/types/recipe.ts
export type RecipeRead = {
  id: number;
  title: string;
  servings: number;
  instructions: string;
  ingredients: RecipeIngredientRead[];
  created_at: string;
};

export type RecipeCreate = {
  title: string;
  servings: number;
  instructions: string;
  ingredients: RecipeIngredientCreate[];
};
```

## Do not

- Do not use `any` — use `unknown` and narrow, or define a proper type.
- Do not pass server data down as props across multiple levels — read from query hooks directly.
- Do not put API calls or React Query calls inside components — extract to `src/hooks/`.
- Do not use class components.
- Do not co-locate test files with source; put them under `src/__tests__/`.
